      "phase_evolution": "During intercritical annealing, Mn and C partition from ferrite to austenite across the α/γ interface, leading to local enrichment of Mn in austenite near the interface. This partitioning, along with differences in grain size, contributes to higher-than-expected austenite stability."
    },
